This is a great little regional Chinese restaurant.  The fried pork intestines are delicious, you should definitely try them.  We got pork with vegetable and bean was also lovely (it’s green beans, sautéed pork belly and fermented black bean sauce).  We also got the pea shoots, which were pricey, but lovely.  This is the only Chinese place that has brought a free desert that is actually worth eating.  It was a coconut gelatine with white beans...it was actually pretty good.

Food was okay.  Came here for dinner service.  The grouper fish casserole with eggplant, tofu, and peppers was good in taste and portion but oily.  The pan fried eel special was prepared well, but the flavor didn't stand out.  Eel would have more flavor if they used pepper salt seasoning.  Chicken was served cold and too much cooking wine in the ginger dipping sauce that paired with the chicken. Service is slow; we were about 75% done with one dish before the next one came out.  The restaurant is clean, simple, and straightforward.  Could use some decor or color for all the white walls.  About 8 tables only, so make reservations in advance if you plan to try this place out.
